00:17:55.579 --> 00:18:02.380
So first up, what are your recommendations for hosting Shiny and making apps available?

00:18:02.739 --> 00:18:04.739
Oh, Pozit-Connect?

00:18:04.739 --> 00:18:06.739
All right.

00:18:06.739 --> 00:18:08.739
Next question.

00:18:08.739 --> 00:18:16.579
How do you evaluate the success of an app beyond requests or user numbers?

00:18:16.579 --> 00:18:17.859
Beyond requests and what?

00:18:17.859 --> 00:18:18.859
User numbers.

00:18:18.859 --> 00:18:19.859
Oh, yeah.

00:18:19.859 --> 00:18:25.579
So let's just say user numbers and all that, it's almost like one of the generic ways.

00:18:25.579 --> 00:18:28.459
It's almost like you can apply it everywhere.

00:18:28.459 --> 00:18:34.140
But think about a Shiny app that would be able to share some of the business insights.

00:18:34.140 --> 00:18:38.819
Those are the ones maybe it's less frequently asked questions that you are getting the answer,

00:18:38.819 --> 00:18:45.520
